snippet.textDisplay: @AIOU INFO I know that our immune system during COVID-19 can either stop the COVID-19 virus cells in the lungs - such as the macrophages - or it can damage the alveolar cells and make the disease worse  - like what happens with the immune cells like the interleukines and TNF-a, and lead to deadly ARDS, and this can happen when the number of viral cells outnumber any immune cells that are recruited to kill off the viruses, right?
